## Coding Standards

### Naming Conventions

**Must be strictly followed**. All code in English only.

| Item | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| **Variables & Functions** | camelCase | `findCandidateById`, `candidateEmail` |
| **Classes & Types** | PascalCase | `Candidate`, `CandidateService`, `CandidateRepository` |
| **Constants** | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_CANDIDATES_PER_PAGE`, `DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE` |
| **Interfaces** | PascalCase (no I prefix) | `CandidateRepository` not `ICandidateRepository` |
| **Files** | camelCase | `candidateService.ts`, `candidateController.ts` |

```typescript
// Good: English, consistent naming
export const MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE_MB = 10;

export class CandidateService {
    async findCandidateById(id: number): Promise<Candidate | null> {
        return this.candidateRepository.findById(id);
    }
}

// Bad: Non-English naming
export const TAM_MAX_UPLOAD_MB = 10;  // Spanish/mixed

export class RepositorioCandidatos {  // Spanish naming
    async buscarPorId(id: number): Promise<any> {
        return this.candidatos.findById(id);  // Spanish variable
    }
}
```

### TypeScript Strict Mode

**Required**: `strict: true` in `tsconfig.json`.

```typescript
// Good: Explicit types, no any
async function findCandidates(limit: number): Promise<Candidate[]> {
    return this.repository.find({ take: limit });
}

// Bad: Missing types, uses any
async function findCandidates(limit): Promise<any> {
    return this.repository.find({ take: limit });
}
```

### Comments: Explain Why, Not What

Comments should explain business logic or non-obvious decisions, not describe code line-by-line.

```typescript
// Good: Explains business reason
async save(candidate: Candidate): Promise<Candidate> {
    // We duplicate the email field for performance-sensitive queries
    // without joining the normalized email table
    return this.repository.save(candidate);
}

// Bad: Redundant comments
async save(candidate: Candidate): Promise<Candidate> {
    // Save the candidate
    return this.repository.save(candidate);  // This saves the candidate
}
```

