## API Design Standards

### REST Conventions

Follow RESTful conventions for all endpoints.

```typescript
// Good: Resource-based, standard HTTP methods
GET    /candidates              // List all candidates
GET    /candidates/:id          // Get candidate by ID
POST   /candidates              // Create new candidate
PUT    /candidates/:id          // Update entire candidate
PATCH  /candidates/:id          // Partial update
DELETE /candidates/:id          // Delete candidate

GET    /candidates/:id/educations  // List candidate's educations
POST   /candidates/:id/educations  // Add education to candidate
```

### Request/Response Format

```typescript
// Success (200 OK, 201 Created, etc.)
{
    "success": true,
    "data": { /* resource */ },
    "message": "Operation completed"
}

// Error (4xx, 5xx)
{
    "success": false,
    "error": {
        "message": "Descriptive error message",
        "code": "ERROR_CODE"
    }
}

// Validation Error (400 Bad Request)
{
    "success": false,
    "error": {
        "message": "Validation failed",
        "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
        "details": [
            { "field": "email", "reason": "Invalid email format" },
            { "field": "firstName", "reason": "Required field" }
        ]
    }
}
```

### Error Status Codes

| Code | Use Case |
|------|----------|
| **400** | Validation failed, bad request |
| **401** | Unauthorized, missing/invalid credentials |
| **403** | Forbidden, authentication passed but access denied |
| **404** | Resource not found |
| **409** | Conflict, e.g., duplicate email |
| **500** | Internal server error |

