## Performance Best Practices

### Async/Await

Always use async/await. Avoid promise chains.

```typescript
// Good: async/await with proper error handling
async function createCandidate(data: CandidateData): Promise<Candidate> {
    try {
        const existing = await repository.findByEmail(data.email);
        if (existing) throw new Error('Email already in use');
        return await repository.save(new Candidate(data));
    } catch (error) {
        throw error;
    }
}

// Parallel operations
const [candidate, positions] = await Promise.all([
    candidateService.findById(1),
    positionService.findAll()
]);
```

### Database Optimization

- Use `include` to prevent N+1 queries
- Add database indexes for frequently queried fields
- Paginate large result sets

```typescript
// Good: Pagination + efficient queries
async function listCandidates(page: number = 1, limit: number = 10): Promise<Candidate[]> {
    return this.repository.find({
        skip: (page - 1) * limit,
        take: limit,
        orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' }
    });
}
```

